  "prompt": "What are the 3 best things you would recommend to improve your questions on Quora?",
  "response": "Improving your questions on Quora can help you get more insightful, accurate, and engaging answers. Here are three recommendations:\n\n### 1. **Be Clear and Specific**\n   - **Why it matters**: Vague or overly broad questions can lead to unclear or irrelevant answers. Clarity ensures that responders understand what you're asking.\n   - **How to do it**: Use precise language, provide context, and avoid ambiguity. For example, instead of asking, \"What\u2019s the best diet?\" you could ask, \"What\u2019s the most effective diet for weight loss for someone with a sedentary lifestyle?\"\n\n### 2. **Add Context or Background**\n   - **Why it matters**: Adding context helps responders tailor their answers to your specific situation or needs.\n   - **How to do it**: Briefly explain why you\u2019re asking the question or provide relevant details. For instance, if asking about career advice, mention your industry, experience level, or goals.\n\n### 3. **Engage the Community Thoughtfully**\n   - **Why it matters**: Quora thrives on thoughtful dialogue. Engaging questions encourage in-depth, meaningful responses.\n   - **How to do it**: Avoid yes/no questions and instead ask open-ended ones that invite discussion. For example, instead of, \"Is Python a good language?\" ask, \"What are the advantages and disadvantages of using Python for data science projects?\"\n\n### Bonus Tip: **Review Before Posting**\n   - Double-check for typos, grammar, and clarity. A well-written question is more likely to attract high-quality answers.\n\nBy following these tips, you\u2019ll increase the likelihood of receiving valuable and relevant responses from the Quora community.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
